1
00:00:08,408 --> 00:00:11,277
<i>My life has always been ordinary.</i>

2
00:00:12,278 --> 00:00:13,847
<i>Something not even worth mentioning.</i>

3
00:00:16,082 --> 00:00:17,951
<i>Whether I remember it or not,</i>

4
00:00:20,186 --> 00:00:21,521
<i>it was never anything special.</i>

5
00:00:23,857 --> 00:00:24,991
<i>No,</i>

6
00:00:25,058 --> 00:00:27,193
<i>if anything,</i>

7
00:00:27,260 --> 00:00:29,095
<i>it's full of memories I'd rather forget.</i>

8
00:00:33,633 --> 00:00:35,468
<i>As a kid,</i>

9
00:00:35,535 --> 00:00:38,171
<i>I never had the courage</i>
<i>to stand up to the bullies.</i>

10
00:00:38,738 --> 00:00:42,108
<i>A girl with a strong sense of justice</i>
<i>just happened to pass by and save me.</i>

11
00:00:46,212 --> 00:00:47,847
<i>And I fell in love for the first time.</i>

12
00:00:50,884 --> 00:00:54,320
<i>But I couldn't even thank her.</i>

13
00:00:58,324 --> 00:01:00,894
<i>In the end, I never worked up</i>
<i>the courage to speak to her.</i>

14
00:01:03,363 --> 00:01:04,264
<i>No matter how long</i>

15
00:01:05,098 --> 00:01:08,802
<i>I waited, the love of my life never came.</i>

16
00:01:11,237 --> 00:01:12,672
<i>I was always just an observer.</i>

17
00:01:15,308 --> 00:01:16,443
<i>That was my life.</i>

18
00:01:18,912 --> 00:01:20,513
<i>And I thought I was okay with it.</i>

19
00:01:23,850 --> 00:01:24,818
<i>But…</i>

20
00:01:27,353 --> 00:01:28,721
<i>the day I met you…</i>

21
00:01:44,838 --> 00:01:46,206
<i>my life…</i>

22
00:01:47,874 --> 00:01:49,075
<i>had changed.</i>

23
00:02:00,019 --> 00:02:05,024
We opened our directly operated
Meguro store on the first of last month,

24
00:02:05,091 --> 00:02:09,662
and we've added 13 new retailers.

25
00:02:09,729 --> 00:02:11,131
We now have 62 locations--

26
00:02:11,197 --> 00:02:13,967
We still don't have enough locations
in central Tokyo.

27
00:02:14,601 --> 00:02:17,237
What about a major shopping complex
attached to a terminal station?

28
00:02:17,303 --> 00:02:18,972
Is there any chance of getting
into NEWoMan Takanawa?

29
00:02:20,173 --> 00:02:22,075
We've approached them several times.

30
00:02:22,142 --> 00:02:24,711
-It isn't so easy--
-Whether Velel gets into that location

31
00:02:24,777 --> 00:02:27,013
could change the company's
overall sales by two or 3%.

32
00:02:27,580 --> 00:02:30,016
IZUMI TAKEDA - MARIKO'S SECRETARY

33
00:02:32,719 --> 00:02:35,054
-Are you saying you can't do it?
-Oh, no,

34
00:02:35,655 --> 00:02:36,489
I'll do my best.

35
00:02:37,123 --> 00:02:38,491
-Please do.
-Yes.

36
00:02:39,359 --> 00:02:41,427
-She's scary…
-Continuing…

37
00:02:41,494 --> 00:02:42,996
TAKUMI SANO, SECOND BRAND DIVISION
RYOKO HASHIMOTO, SECOND BRAND DIVISION

38
00:02:43,763 --> 00:02:45,598
Please schedule a meeting
with Ms. Hara from NEWoMan.

39
00:02:45,665 --> 00:02:46,799
I'll speak with her personally.

40
00:02:46,866 --> 00:02:48,201
Understood.

41
00:02:48,268 --> 00:02:51,905
I'd like to discuss this
with the branch's president.

42
00:02:51,971 --> 00:02:53,206
Make sure you tell them that.

43
00:02:53,273 --> 00:02:55,008
-I will let them know.
-Did you hear?

44
00:02:55,074 --> 00:02:57,110
Apparently, Mariko has seriously started

45
00:02:57,177 --> 00:02:59,879
-looking for a husband.
-What? Really?

46
00:03:01,848 --> 00:03:02,682
-Excuse me.
-I hear

47
00:03:02,749 --> 00:03:05,218
-she's been on some dates already.
-What? Seriously?

48
00:03:37,650 --> 00:03:40,486
Another date that didn't go well?

49
00:03:42,322 --> 00:03:44,357
Don't say "another".

50
00:03:44,424 --> 00:03:45,592
So I was right.

51
00:03:47,794 --> 00:03:51,364
I mean, we just had nothing in common.

52
00:03:52,165 --> 00:03:55,034
He asked me what I do on my days off,

53
00:03:55,101 --> 00:03:56,569
so I said I watch movies,

54
00:03:56,636 --> 00:03:59,272
and from there, he spent the rest
of the conversation talking about <i>Top Gun.</i>

55
00:03:59,339 --> 00:04:01,774
He was trying to connect with you.

56
00:04:01,841 --> 00:04:03,643
I've never even seen <i>Top Gun.</i>

57
00:04:03,710 --> 00:04:06,246
When I told him that, he said, "Seriously?

58
00:04:06,312 --> 00:04:08,081
You're missing out on life!"

59
00:04:08,147 --> 00:04:11,284
Yes, I know that type of person.

60
00:04:11,351 --> 00:04:14,220
-They're annoying, aren't they?
-Yes, I know.

61
00:04:14,287 --> 00:04:17,090
But this time, it's your fault.

62
00:04:17,991 --> 00:04:19,158
What? Why?

63
00:04:19,225 --> 00:04:22,061
Because you only watch
Marvel superhero movies.

64
00:04:23,630 --> 00:04:27,333
You don't watch movies on your day off.

65
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:29,902
You have to say Marvel movies.

66
00:04:29,969 --> 00:04:31,638
That's why he brought up <i>Top Gun.</i>

67
00:04:35,275 --> 00:04:39,045
Still, that's what dating for marriage is.

68
00:04:40,179 --> 00:04:43,783
It's about figuring out each other's
boring parts and weird quirks,

69
00:04:43,850 --> 00:04:46,152
then finding someone
you can compromise with.

70
00:04:47,587 --> 00:04:49,289
That's marriage hunting.

71
00:04:51,257 --> 00:04:55,061
Though I guess it's funny hearing that
from someone who's divorced.

72
00:04:57,263 --> 00:04:59,165
But it's okay.

73
00:05:01,167 --> 00:05:03,803
My marriage gave me
the greatest treasure of my life.

74
00:05:09,409 --> 00:05:10,543
You don't seriously

75
00:05:11,144 --> 00:05:16,449
expect to meet someone
where you instantly click, do you?

76
00:05:17,750 --> 00:05:23,389
You don't actually believe in destiny,
do you?

77
00:05:24,791 --> 00:05:27,593
Of course not. I don't believe in that.

78
00:05:27,660 --> 00:05:29,128
Let me assure you.

79
00:05:29,829 --> 00:05:31,497
There's no such thing.

80
00:05:39,872 --> 00:05:40,873
Thank you for waiting.

81
00:05:40,940 --> 00:05:42,875
Here's the daily lunch special.

82
00:05:42,942 --> 00:05:44,243
Thank you very much.

83
00:05:48,147 --> 00:05:49,515
-Thank you.
-Sure.

84
00:05:50,616 --> 00:05:54,554
VELEL BEGINS ITS SKINCARE DEPARTMENT

85
00:05:54,620 --> 00:05:57,156
DAD: CAN WE TALK ABOUT
THAT PROPOSAL FROM THE OTHER DAY?

86
00:06:01,594 --> 00:06:03,262
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

87
00:06:03,329 --> 00:06:04,464
-Credit card, please.
-Okay.

88
00:06:05,231 --> 00:06:08,234
That'll be 2,000 yen.

89
00:06:08,301 --> 00:06:09,135
-Okay.
-Thank you.

90
00:06:10,103 --> 00:06:12,071
-Okay.
-Just touch here, please.

91
00:06:16,109 --> 00:06:17,510
-Ah, one more time, please.
-Okay.

92
00:06:20,346 --> 00:06:23,449
Sorry. I think the machine just broke.

93
00:06:24,250 --> 00:06:26,119
Sorry, do you have cash?

94
00:06:27,353 --> 00:06:29,422
I didn't bring any cash.

95
00:06:30,957 --> 00:06:32,725
-I'm sorry.
-Well then…

96
00:06:32,792 --> 00:06:34,026
You can put hers together with mine.

97
00:06:34,594 --> 00:06:35,762
No, you don't have to.

98
00:06:37,296 --> 00:06:38,131
Together.

99
00:06:39,098 --> 00:06:39,932
Thank you.

100
00:06:41,367 --> 00:06:42,268
Okay then…

101
00:06:42,335 --> 00:06:44,404
-All right, thank you.
-Sure.

102
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:50,476
-Excuse me!
-Yes?

103
00:06:51,511 --> 00:06:53,045
-Thank you very much.
-No, not at all.

104
00:06:54,147 --> 00:06:56,349
I can send it back to you
with a payment app.

105
00:06:56,416 --> 00:06:57,383
That's okay.

106
00:06:57,450 --> 00:07:01,187
I can't let a complete stranger
pay for my lunch.

107
00:07:02,855 --> 00:07:05,091
Would you rather have cash?

108
00:07:05,158 --> 00:07:07,326
If so, I can send it to you later.

109
00:07:07,393 --> 00:07:09,162
Just give me your contact information

110
00:07:14,667 --> 00:07:15,935
Um…

111
00:07:16,636 --> 00:07:18,004
I'm not trying to do anything.

112
00:07:19,305 --> 00:07:21,541
-I'm sorry.
-I know.

113
00:07:24,710 --> 00:07:25,978
You know?

114
00:07:37,557 --> 00:07:40,693
GINJIRO NOSE
MARIKO'S FATHER AND PRESIDENT

115
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:43,196
VELEL BEGINS ITS SKINCARE DEPARTMENT

116
00:07:47,266 --> 00:07:48,734
Your cost estimates are too optimistic.

117
00:07:50,136 --> 00:07:52,672
You should be able to lower
the production cost further.

118
00:07:52,738 --> 00:07:53,573
Understood.

119
00:07:54,574 --> 00:07:56,042
The ingredients aren't that great either.

120
00:07:56,609 --> 00:07:58,110
GOTA ASAI, GINJIRO'S SECRETARY

121
00:07:58,177 --> 00:08:01,647
As it stands, I don't see how launching
a skincare line under Velel

122
00:08:01,714 --> 00:08:03,950
has much chance of succeeding.

123
00:08:05,985 --> 00:08:06,853
I understand.

124
00:08:08,955 --> 00:08:11,090
Revise it before the executive meeting.

125
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:15,628
Thank you very much.

126
00:08:20,299 --> 00:08:21,300
It's been decided?

127
00:08:21,367 --> 00:08:22,535
Pretty much.

128
00:08:22,602 --> 00:08:24,470
-You did it!
-You really did.

129
00:08:24,537 --> 00:08:26,906
If we add skincare alongside makeup,

130
00:08:26,973 --> 00:08:29,275
Velel could become
the company's top brand.

131
00:08:29,342 --> 00:08:30,843
I hope it sells!

132
00:08:30,910 --> 00:08:31,978
It definitely will!

133
00:08:32,044 --> 00:08:33,746
Stem cells are really popular right now.

134
00:08:33,813 --> 00:08:35,748
Nothing has been decided yet.

135
00:08:35,815 --> 00:08:37,116
We still have a lot of issues to solve.

136
00:08:42,021 --> 00:08:43,589
I see.

137
00:08:43,656 --> 00:08:46,058
So the ingredients need
to be rethought as well.

138
00:08:48,127 --> 00:08:51,664
Using PDRN as-is doesn't make us unique.

139
00:08:53,032 --> 00:08:54,333
We need something original…

140
00:09:00,506 --> 00:09:02,675
I heard.

141
00:09:02,742 --> 00:09:06,279
Velel's starting a skincare division, huh?

142
00:09:06,345 --> 00:09:07,179
Congratulations.

143
00:09:08,514 --> 00:09:11,717
-Nothing has been decided yet.
-It practically has.

144
00:09:12,652 --> 00:09:14,520
People say you and the president
don't get along,

145
00:09:15,021 --> 00:09:19,191
but I guess he still
has a soft spot for his daughter.

146
00:09:37,977 --> 00:09:39,946
<i>Doors are closing.</i>

147
00:09:40,880 --> 00:09:42,515
-I'm sorry.
-Excuse me.

148
00:09:42,582 --> 00:09:43,416
Sorry.

149
00:09:49,388 --> 00:09:50,790
Sorry about that.

150
00:09:55,194 --> 00:09:57,396
So you said "I know"
because you're our employee?

151
00:10:00,066 --> 00:10:00,900
Excuse me.

152
00:10:00,967 --> 00:10:03,336
Oh, wait.

153
00:10:03,402 --> 00:10:04,236
For lunch…

154
00:10:04,303 --> 00:10:07,073
-Really, don't worry about it.
-No.

155
00:10:07,139 --> 00:10:09,141
There's no reason for you to buy me lunch.

156
00:10:10,443 --> 00:10:12,612
-Thanks for helping me.
-Okay then…

157
00:10:14,981 --> 00:10:18,017
Oh, uh, this isn't mine.

158
00:10:18,684 --> 00:10:19,385
SKINCARE MARKET RESEARCH

159
00:10:19,452 --> 00:10:21,854
That's mine.

160
00:10:23,556 --> 00:10:25,057
You did this?

161
00:10:26,892 --> 00:10:30,329
There have been a lot of Korean products

162
00:10:30,396 --> 00:10:33,165
using stem cell culture
supernatant lately,

163
00:10:33,232 --> 00:10:36,769
so I thought I'd learn more about it.

164
00:10:43,175 --> 00:10:45,444
If we combine it
with plant-derived stem cells,

165
00:10:45,511 --> 00:10:48,080
I think we could develop
something ourselves.

166
00:10:48,147 --> 00:10:50,149
We could get ahead of the competition.

167
00:10:53,219 --> 00:10:56,389
Ah, sorry, I shouldn't act like
I know what I'm talking about.

168
00:10:58,324 --> 00:10:59,925
Which department do you work in?

169
00:11:01,661 --> 00:11:03,362
<i>Going up.</i>

170
00:11:04,030 --> 00:11:05,364
These are the approval documents

171
00:11:05,431 --> 00:11:07,733
for our current product
development projects.

172
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:09,235
Who's that?

173
00:11:09,301 --> 00:11:12,204
I think he's Yukimura
from General Affairs.

174
00:11:12,271 --> 00:11:13,072
SOTA YUKIMURA, GENERAL AFFAIRS

175
00:11:13,139 --> 00:11:16,375
People in General Affairs
say he's completely harmless.

176
00:11:16,442 --> 00:11:17,843
The invisible type.

177
00:11:17,910 --> 00:11:22,581
So why is this invisible guy
joining our department?

178
00:11:23,516 --> 00:11:25,851
If you have any questions, just ask.

179
00:11:25,918 --> 00:11:26,752
Um…

180
00:11:27,953 --> 00:11:30,022
Why was I transferred here?

181
00:11:30,690 --> 00:11:34,460
Because Mariko believes
you're someone who could come in handy.

182
00:11:44,837 --> 00:11:46,205
Look, look. Mariko's here.

183
00:11:47,273 --> 00:11:49,275
-Hey.
-Yes?

184
00:11:51,177 --> 00:11:54,046
Could you write a proposal after looking
into whether we could use those

185
00:11:54,113 --> 00:11:56,582
plant-derived stem cell ingredients
you mentioned the other day?

186
00:11:56,649 --> 00:12:01,520
Oh, uh, well, the papers
I read didn't include

187
00:12:01,587 --> 00:12:03,322
-any in vivo test results.
-So you can't do it?

188
00:12:03,389 --> 00:12:04,423
No, no.

189
00:12:05,157 --> 00:12:06,158
I can if I have the data.

190
00:12:06,726 --> 00:12:09,628
I ordered some. I'll send it to you later.

191
00:12:09,695 --> 00:12:10,963
Thank you.

192
00:12:25,745 --> 00:12:26,812
I understand.

193
00:12:27,646 --> 00:12:30,182
Mariko is a bit scary, isn't she?

194
00:12:30,249 --> 00:12:33,185
I couldn't even tell
why she was angry just now.

195
00:12:33,252 --> 00:12:36,689
Was she angry? I thought
she was just giving me instructions.

196
00:12:38,157 --> 00:12:41,727
Yukimura, are you one of those people
who's weirdly immune to pressure?

197
00:12:43,496 --> 00:12:44,330
I'm not sure.

198
00:12:51,237 --> 00:12:52,772
I'm surprised.

199
00:12:52,838 --> 00:12:55,074
So that's your type, huh?

200
00:12:55,975 --> 00:12:57,977
-What are you talking about?
-Yukimura.

201
00:12:59,645 --> 00:13:00,513
What?

202
00:13:00,579 --> 00:13:04,016
It's the first time I've ever seen you
take an interest in someone.

203
00:13:04,083 --> 00:13:05,518
Only professionally.

204
00:13:05,584 --> 00:13:07,653
-Oh, look, look.
-Stop that.

205
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:10,656
-You're blushing.
-Honestly…

206
00:13:11,223 --> 00:13:14,293
Wow, a guy like him, huh…

207
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:15,694
GRANDMA: COME SEE ME AFTER WORK,
I HAVE SOMETHING IMPORTANT TO TALK ABOUT

208
00:13:30,509 --> 00:13:32,945
AKIKO NOSE, MARIKO'S GRANDMOTHER

209
00:13:34,146 --> 00:13:36,315
So, what's the important thing?

210
00:13:36,949 --> 00:13:40,152
Your grandma has finally met
her person of destiny.

211
00:13:40,953 --> 00:13:41,921
What?

212
00:13:41,987 --> 00:13:44,690
I stopped by one of our clients today,

213
00:13:44,757 --> 00:13:48,427
and on the way home, I found a man
at a vegetable stand selling potatoes,

214
00:13:48,494 --> 00:13:51,030
and he said, "They're only 500 yen."

215
00:13:51,096 --> 00:13:52,031
I see…

216
00:13:52,097 --> 00:13:55,568
But they got so heavy,
I couldn't continue walking.

217
00:13:55,634 --> 00:13:57,236
Really? Are you okay?

218
00:13:57,303 --> 00:14:01,340
A wonderful young man
happened to come by and help me.

219
00:14:03,642 --> 00:14:05,544
Your person of destiny is a young man?

220
00:14:06,612 --> 00:14:09,448
Older than you, I'd say.

221
00:14:11,517 --> 00:14:14,053
He's a good person.

222
00:14:14,119 --> 00:14:17,223
Perfect husband material for you.

223
00:14:17,289 --> 00:14:20,292
Is that what this was about?

224
00:14:20,359 --> 00:14:22,061
You're looking for someone
to marry, aren't you?

225
00:14:22,695 --> 00:14:23,996
Or have you found someone already?

226
00:14:24,897 --> 00:14:25,998
No, but…

227
00:14:26,065 --> 00:14:29,301
I arranged for the three of us
to meet tomorrow.

228
00:14:30,536 --> 00:14:31,604
What?!

229
00:14:32,171 --> 00:14:34,506
Why would you do that without asking me?

230
00:14:34,573 --> 00:14:35,808
-Like I said, it's for your…
-What?

231
00:14:36,408 --> 00:14:37,810
Mariko's proposal?

232
00:14:39,511 --> 00:14:41,947
I think the president
intends to approve it.

233
00:14:42,014 --> 00:14:43,782
If that happens,

234
00:14:43,849 --> 00:14:46,819
her position inside the company
will only get stronger!

235
00:14:46,886 --> 00:14:48,153
What have you been doing?

236
00:14:48,888 --> 00:14:50,256
I'm sorry.

237
00:14:50,322 --> 00:14:51,523
<i>Keito won't be joining the company</i>

238
00:14:51,590 --> 00:14:54,860
and becoming an executive
for another five years.

239
00:14:55,728 --> 00:14:57,563
Stop this, no matter what it takes.

240
00:14:57,630 --> 00:14:58,797
I know.

241
00:14:59,531 --> 00:15:01,000
I've already set things in motion.

242
00:15:02,134 --> 00:15:03,235
Are you sure about this?

243
00:15:03,302 --> 00:15:06,505
You don't even know who the man is.

244
00:15:07,072 --> 00:15:09,341
-Oh, sis! You're here.
-Yes.

245
00:15:09,408 --> 00:15:12,444
That serum sample you gave me
the other day was great.

246
00:15:12,511 --> 00:15:13,946
Can I have another one?

247
00:15:14,013 --> 00:15:15,981
-Another one?
-Please. One more. Please.

248
00:15:16,982 --> 00:15:19,084
-Hello.
-Sure, fine…

249
00:15:19,151 --> 00:15:21,186
Oh, Mariko, you're here.

250
00:15:21,253 --> 00:15:22,087
Yes.

251
00:15:22,154 --> 00:15:23,522
Have you eaten yet?

252
00:15:23,589 --> 00:15:26,425
-Why don't we have something together?
-That's right. We should.

253
00:15:26,492 --> 00:15:28,027
It's been a while
since we've all eaten together.

254
00:15:30,095 --> 00:15:32,731
I'll pass. I've got plans with friends.

255
00:15:32,798 --> 00:15:35,234
Hey, Keito, you little…

256
00:15:35,301 --> 00:15:38,637
I still have work to do,
so I'd better get going.

257
00:15:38,704 --> 00:15:40,940
-I see…
-Oh, that's too bad.

258
00:15:41,006 --> 00:15:42,374
Come by again anytime.

259
00:15:54,086 --> 00:15:58,324
MARIKO

260
00:16:14,673 --> 00:16:15,674
Hey…

261
00:16:16,742 --> 00:16:17,977
I think I'm just going to leave.

262
00:16:18,043 --> 00:16:19,578
Don't worry.

263
00:16:19,645 --> 00:16:20,813
He's a good man.

264
00:16:22,748 --> 00:16:24,616
Oh, over here!

265
00:16:29,288 --> 00:16:31,156
Sorry to keep you waiting.

266
00:16:39,531 --> 00:16:40,632
I'm sorry.

267
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:44,236
I was just surprised
by how beautiful you are.

268
00:16:45,304 --> 00:16:47,473
Ah, what am I saying?

269
00:16:48,807 --> 00:16:52,011
This is my granddaughter, Mariko.

270
00:16:53,012 --> 00:16:55,180
This is Taisuke Sakura.

271
00:16:56,081 --> 00:16:59,485
-It's nice to meet you. My name is Sakura.
-Nice to meet you.

272
00:17:01,253 --> 00:17:03,756
Thank you for helping my grandmother

273
00:17:03,822 --> 00:17:05,124
-the other day.
-No, not at all.

274
00:17:07,893 --> 00:17:11,597
-Well, first, let's sit down.
-Of course.

275
00:17:14,233 --> 00:17:16,935
I forgot to ask before.

276
00:17:17,002 --> 00:17:19,738
What do you do for a living, Mr. Sakura?

277
00:17:21,340 --> 00:17:22,408
I'm a civil servant.

278
00:17:22,474 --> 00:17:24,643
Oh, that's wonderful.

279
00:17:24,710 --> 00:17:26,612
Perfect husband material.

280
00:17:26,678 --> 00:17:28,647
Grandma, don't be so pushy.

281
00:17:28,714 --> 00:17:30,115
You're making him uncomfortable.

282
00:17:31,850 --> 00:17:35,154
To be honest, I almost didn't come.

283
00:17:35,988 --> 00:17:38,657
You just suddenly wanted me
to meet your granddaughter.

284
00:17:39,958 --> 00:17:41,126
I'm very sorry.

285
00:17:42,127 --> 00:17:45,564
But I'm glad I came.

286
00:18:00,846 --> 00:18:01,947
Hello?

287
00:18:02,481 --> 00:18:04,716
I need you to do something for me.

288
00:18:15,627 --> 00:18:16,829
Good work today, everyone.

289
00:18:16,895 --> 00:18:17,930
I'm heading out.

290
00:18:17,996 --> 00:18:19,631
-You as well.
-Have a good day.

291
00:18:20,766 --> 00:18:24,536
As always, she leaves right on time.

292
00:18:24,603 --> 00:18:27,406
That's fine. It makes it easier
for us to leave too.

293
00:18:27,473 --> 00:18:28,373
That's true.

294
00:18:30,309 --> 00:18:31,143
All right then…

295
00:18:35,114 --> 00:18:37,449
VELVEL SKINCARE PROGRESS REPORT

296
00:18:38,951 --> 00:18:39,985
Pardon me.

297
00:18:42,154 --> 00:18:43,222
Thank you.

298
00:18:44,156 --> 00:18:45,858
You've been coming here a lot lately.

299
00:18:47,426 --> 00:18:48,560
Sorry for staying so long.

300
00:18:48,627 --> 00:18:51,029
Not at all. You're always welcome.

301
00:18:53,232 --> 00:18:54,666
Take your time.

302
00:18:56,135 --> 00:18:57,035
Good luck.

303
00:19:15,120 --> 00:19:16,021
Hello.

304
00:19:18,824 --> 00:19:20,425
I thought you'd already gone home.

305
00:19:20,492 --> 00:19:24,363
You come back to work
at night a lot, don't you?

306
00:19:25,731 --> 00:19:26,832
I was wondering.

307
00:19:26,899 --> 00:19:28,467
Do you pretend to leave on time

308
00:19:28,534 --> 00:19:32,237
so your staff will feel comfortable
going home?

309
00:19:34,506 --> 00:19:35,507
Um,

310
00:19:36,208 --> 00:19:38,210
I don't know if you'll like it, but…

311
00:19:39,278 --> 00:19:41,446
-No, isn't that for you?
-No, no,

312
00:19:41,513 --> 00:19:43,482
I bought one for myself too.

313
00:19:49,755 --> 00:19:52,925
Is this from that old
traditional-style cafe behind the office?

314
00:19:52,991 --> 00:19:56,094
Visiting cafes is one of my hobbies.

315
00:19:56,895 --> 00:19:59,164
I've been there too.

316
00:20:00,732 --> 00:20:03,402
I wanted to keep it as my secret hideaway.

317
00:20:04,770 --> 00:20:07,272
Then I won't go anymore.

318
00:20:08,607 --> 00:20:13,111
What? Oh, no, that's not what I meant.

319
00:20:13,178 --> 00:20:15,647
Cafes belong to everyone.

320
00:20:24,623 --> 00:20:25,524
Your phone…

321
00:20:28,560 --> 00:20:30,796
Iguazu Falls, in Argentina.

322
00:20:31,663 --> 00:20:32,698
You've been there?

323
00:20:33,999 --> 00:20:34,900
Yes.

324
00:20:36,068 --> 00:20:40,839
Actually, it was used
as a filming location in a Marvel movie.

325
00:20:40,906 --> 00:20:42,874
I'm a huge Marvel fan.

326
00:20:44,109 --> 00:20:47,112
People think Marvel movies
are just superhero films,

327
00:20:47,846 --> 00:20:50,682
but they're actually
full of deep human drama.

328
00:20:50,749 --> 00:20:54,653
Each hero has their own
standalone story, but then they all

329
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:58,957
come together in the Avengers movies,
like a giant puzzle.

330
00:20:59,024 --> 00:21:00,359
It's so exciting.

331
00:21:07,799 --> 00:21:09,668
Why am I getting so carried away?

332
00:21:09,735 --> 00:21:10,736
Oops.

333
00:21:13,939 --> 00:21:16,108
The Warrior Falls, from <i>Black Panther.</i>

334
00:21:21,213 --> 00:21:24,149
I've been there too.

335
00:21:27,986 --> 00:21:30,555
You're the first person I've ever
been able to have this conversation with.

336
00:21:32,758 --> 00:21:35,093
I've actually visited a lot
of other Marvel locations too.

337
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:39,431
The first one I went to
was Grand Central Terminal in New York.

338
00:21:39,498 --> 00:21:40,766
Look, look.

339
00:21:42,668 --> 00:21:45,637
Standing there thinking,
"This is where the Avengers fought."

340
00:21:48,173 --> 00:21:49,074
Oh, sorry.

341
00:21:50,642 --> 00:21:52,244
I must seem creepy,
talking your ear off like this.

342
00:21:54,746 --> 00:21:55,614
I'm really sorry.

343
00:22:14,766 --> 00:22:15,967
What?

344
00:22:16,034 --> 00:22:18,470
What? What?

345
00:22:18,537 --> 00:22:19,571
What is this?

346
00:22:19,638 --> 00:22:22,074
It's practically identical to ours.

347
00:22:22,140 --> 00:22:24,009
Mr. Tateiwa's team

348
00:22:24,076 --> 00:22:26,545
already submitted this proposal
to the company.

349
00:22:26,611 --> 00:22:28,547
No way. They totally stole it.

350
00:22:28,613 --> 00:22:32,818
Apparently, they've already secured
a major partnership too.

351
00:22:33,785 --> 00:22:35,654
I don't think we have any chance now.

352
00:22:39,257 --> 00:22:41,393
Aren't you ashamed using
such underhanded tactics?

353
00:22:41,460 --> 00:22:42,761
Underhanded?

354
00:22:42,828 --> 00:22:44,162
What are you talking about?

355
00:22:44,796 --> 00:22:48,133
You're the ones who came up
with a similar proposal afterward

356
00:22:49,901 --> 00:22:55,707
and tried to use your influence
as the president's daughter to steal ours.

357
00:22:55,774 --> 00:22:57,843
-What are you talking about?
-You…

358
00:22:59,077 --> 00:23:02,347
…really believe you're here
because of your own ability, don't you?

359
00:23:04,783 --> 00:23:07,652
A spoiled little rich girl like you
should know her place.

360
00:23:47,859 --> 00:23:49,828
You can stop.

361
00:23:49,895 --> 00:23:51,363
There's no point anymore.

362
00:23:54,733 --> 00:23:55,901
I know.

363
00:23:56,835 --> 00:23:57,969
But I still want to see it through.

364
00:24:03,175 --> 00:24:04,309
I'VE ATTACHED SUPPORTING MATERIALS

365
00:24:04,376 --> 00:24:05,510
PLEASE CHECK
THE SEPARATE DOCUMENT. YUKIMURA

366
00:24:09,648 --> 00:24:12,851
It's useless! None of this matters!

367
00:24:16,855 --> 00:24:18,290
I know.

368
00:24:20,625 --> 00:24:22,694
I know how serious…

369
00:24:24,062 --> 00:24:25,864
and how much time you've devoted…

370
00:24:29,568 --> 00:24:30,469
to this project.

371
00:24:41,613 --> 00:24:42,647
What?

372
00:25:25,257 --> 00:25:26,157
Excuse me.

373
00:25:33,498 --> 00:25:34,332
What?

374
00:25:34,399 --> 00:25:37,235
I was planning to approve
Tateiwa's project,

375
00:25:38,670 --> 00:25:39,804
but we're going with yours.

376
00:25:41,039 --> 00:25:43,441
-Why all of a sudden?
-Where are the documents?

377
00:25:44,910 --> 00:25:46,578
They're all ready.

378
00:25:46,645 --> 00:25:50,649
We'll announce it officially
at the executive meeting, then.

379
00:25:54,019 --> 00:25:55,153
Thank you.

380
00:25:58,590 --> 00:25:59,891
<i>Congratulations!</i>

381
00:25:59,958 --> 00:26:01,693
It got approved.

382
00:26:01,760 --> 00:26:02,594
Yes.

383
00:26:03,094 --> 00:26:04,930
How did that happen?

384
00:26:04,996 --> 00:26:06,398
Seriously. What changed all of a sudden?

385
00:26:06,464 --> 00:26:08,433
-Right?
-But…

386
00:26:09,134 --> 00:26:10,535
-Yay!
-Yay!

387
00:26:10,602 --> 00:26:11,736
-Yay!
-That's great!

388
00:26:11,803 --> 00:26:13,471
-All right! That's great!
-That's great, that's great!

389
00:26:13,538 --> 00:26:14,673
-Yes!
-Yes.

390
00:26:14,739 --> 00:26:16,474
It's still too early to celebrate.

391
00:26:17,142 --> 00:26:20,211
Contact the research lab immediately
and begin developing the formulation.

392
00:26:20,278 --> 00:26:21,279
-Okay.
-Okay.

393
00:26:21,346 --> 00:26:23,848
Once they have the formulation down,

394
00:26:23,915 --> 00:26:27,552
being strategizing on PR
to get the biggest pull of consumers.

395
00:26:28,286 --> 00:26:31,656
<i>There's no one at our company</i>
<i>who doesn't know Mariko.</i>

396
00:26:34,960 --> 00:26:36,328
Please get me an appointment

397
00:26:36,394 --> 00:26:38,096
with the supervisor of that.
I'll speak with them.

398
00:26:38,163 --> 00:26:39,931
Understood.

399
00:26:39,998 --> 00:26:43,535
<i>She's always the center of attention,</i>
<i>someone who lives in the spotlight.</i>

400
00:26:46,071 --> 00:26:48,540
<i>I was always content…</i>

401
00:26:51,610 --> 00:26:53,812
<i>just watching her from afar.</i>

402
00:26:54,646 --> 00:26:56,448
-I will let them know.
-Did you hear?

403
00:26:56,514 --> 00:26:58,116
Apparently, Mariko has seriously started

404
00:26:58,183 --> 00:27:00,552
-looking for a husband.
-What? Really?

405
00:27:02,520 --> 00:27:04,122
<i>A day like this would of course come.</i>

406
00:27:05,256 --> 00:27:06,391
Welcome in.

407
00:27:06,458 --> 00:27:07,559
Take your time.

408
00:27:08,793 --> 00:27:09,928
<i>I knew someone other than me</i>

409
00:27:11,496 --> 00:27:13,064
<i>would one day be sitting beside her.</i>

410
00:27:14,966 --> 00:27:18,370
<i>I thought I was prepared, but it hurt…</i>

411
00:27:21,272 --> 00:27:22,540
<i>more than I expected.</i>

412
00:27:24,542 --> 00:27:26,411
<i>Watching Mariko from afar…</i>

413
00:27:27,679 --> 00:27:29,080
<i>That was enough.</i>

414
00:27:29,648 --> 00:27:30,982
Sorry.

415
00:27:31,049 --> 00:27:33,852
-I think the machine just broke.
-<i>It should have…</i>

416
00:27:34,919 --> 00:27:36,721
Do you have cash?

417
00:27:36,788 --> 00:27:38,823
I didn't bring any cash.

418
00:27:40,959 --> 00:27:42,627
<i>I thought it would be enough.</i>

419
00:27:46,498 --> 00:27:47,866
You can put hers together with mine.

420
00:27:50,535 --> 00:27:51,870
No, you don't have to.

421
00:27:53,004 --> 00:27:54,139
<i>Life…</i>

422
00:27:54,205 --> 00:27:56,007
It definitely will! Stem cells

423
00:27:56,074 --> 00:27:58,843
-are really popular right now.
-<i>…sometimes changes unexpectedly.</i>

424
00:27:59,344 --> 00:28:00,779
We still have a lot of issues to solve.

425
00:28:02,514 --> 00:28:04,716
<i>I want to help Mariko.</i>

426
00:28:05,216 --> 00:28:07,752
GENERAL AFFAIRS DEPARTMENT

427
00:28:09,721 --> 00:28:11,356
TRENDING INGREDIENTS IN KOREA 2026

428
00:28:11,423 --> 00:28:12,757
<i>I just want to help her.</i>

429
00:28:13,825 --> 00:28:15,393
SKINCARE MARKET RESEARCH

430
00:28:30,809 --> 00:28:33,778
<i>-Really, that's all.</i>
-I'm sorry.

431
00:28:34,479 --> 00:28:35,380
What?

432
00:28:36,481 --> 00:28:38,650
TRANSFER TO THE BRAND DIVISION

433
00:28:43,254 --> 00:28:45,256
<i>I want Mariko to be happy.</i>

434
00:28:45,323 --> 00:28:47,692
PHOTOOS

435
00:28:47,759 --> 00:28:49,427
MARIKO

436
00:28:49,494 --> 00:28:50,762
A NEW FAV SPOT I FOUND

437
00:28:50,829 --> 00:28:52,163
THE ATMOSPHERE IS SO GREAT
YOU FORGET ABOUT TIME

438
00:28:52,731 --> 00:28:54,265
<i>That's all.</i>

439
00:28:54,332 --> 00:28:55,734
ANCIENT FOLK HOUSE
WOOD HEARTH

440
00:28:55,800 --> 00:28:57,936
Is this from that old
traditional-style cafe behind the office?

441
00:28:58,002 --> 00:28:59,904
Visiting cafes is one of my hobbies.

442
00:29:01,106 --> 00:29:05,944
You really believe you're here
because of your own ability, don't you?

443
00:29:06,911 --> 00:29:10,115
A spoiled little rich girl
like you should know her place.

444
00:29:18,623 --> 00:29:19,724
<i>Mariko…</i>

445
00:29:24,329 --> 00:29:26,164
<i>Mariko is hurt,</i>

446
00:29:27,966 --> 00:29:30,101
<i>and I'm just watching.</i>

447
00:29:33,505 --> 00:29:34,873
APPLICANT: TSUYOSHI TATEIWA

448
00:29:36,708 --> 00:29:37,709
<i>No.</i>

449
00:29:37,776 --> 00:29:38,843
TSUYOSHI TATIEWA'S PROPOSAL
TO NOSE COSMETICS

450
00:29:38,910 --> 00:29:40,512
<i>I have to protect Mariko.</i>

451
00:29:44,516 --> 00:29:45,884
<i>I will make sure.</i>

452
00:29:47,118 --> 00:29:48,052
<i>I will.</i>

453
00:29:53,258 --> 00:29:54,092
Excuse me.

454
00:30:02,233 --> 00:30:06,738
I have evidence that you
obtained that partnership through fraud.

455
00:30:07,405 --> 00:30:08,306
Who the hell are you?

456
00:30:08,373 --> 00:30:09,741
PLEASE WALK YOUR BICYCLE

457
00:30:09,808 --> 00:30:14,245
If you don't want this exposed,
withdraw from the new project.

458
00:30:14,913 --> 00:30:16,114
What?

459
00:30:16,181 --> 00:30:18,183
You claimed you landed
the partnership legitimately,

460
00:30:19,083 --> 00:30:22,020
but you paid money to the agency
with company funds, didn't you?

461
00:30:22,086 --> 00:30:26,991
This transfer labeled "preliminary market
research expenses" is suspicious.

462
00:30:27,559 --> 00:30:29,327
-Also…
-You…

463
00:30:30,428 --> 00:30:31,796
work in the brand division, don't you?

464
00:30:33,364 --> 00:30:34,999
Did that spoiled princess
put you up to this?

465
00:30:36,067 --> 00:30:38,736
If this comes to light,
you won't just lose your job.

466
00:30:38,803 --> 00:30:40,271
You'll be facing criminal charges.

467
00:30:41,739 --> 00:30:42,740
Hey!

468
00:30:47,145 --> 00:30:49,247
How did you even get those documents?

469
00:30:50,915 --> 00:30:55,053
You're the one who illegally
accessed company data.

470
00:31:00,325 --> 00:31:01,392
Mariko

471
00:31:02,827 --> 00:31:05,997
isn't treated specially just because she's
the president's daughter. She works hard.

472
00:31:07,966 --> 00:31:09,367
Harder than anyone else.

473
00:31:11,836 --> 00:31:15,473
Every single day, she works
with everything she's got.

474
00:31:17,976 --> 00:31:18,977
I don't get what you mean.

475
00:31:23,915 --> 00:31:26,818
-Hey.
-Please, withdraw.

476
00:31:28,052 --> 00:31:31,456
If you withdraw, I won't tell anyone.
Please, withdraw.

477
00:31:31,522 --> 00:31:32,490
Get out of my way.

478
00:31:33,758 --> 00:31:37,328
-Hey! Let go. Let go!
-Please, withdraw. Please!

479
00:31:39,030 --> 00:31:40,465
What is wrong with you?

480
00:31:41,399 --> 00:31:43,067
Are you crazy or something?

481
00:31:44,736 --> 00:31:46,504
-Hey.
-Please withdraw.

482
00:31:47,272 --> 00:31:48,373
Please withdraw!

483
00:31:48,439 --> 00:31:50,308
Please! Please!

484
00:31:51,109 --> 00:31:51,943
Please withdraw!

485
00:31:57,115 --> 00:31:58,182
I won't tell anyone.

486
00:32:07,258 --> 00:32:11,763
Please continue with the strategy
for PR that we have.

487
00:32:11,829 --> 00:32:16,334
Please decide the release date
by next Friday with Izumi.

488
00:32:16,401 --> 00:32:17,735
-Okay.
-Understood.

489
00:32:20,772 --> 00:32:22,373
Huh? What happened to your mouth?

490
00:32:23,908 --> 00:32:25,443
I just fell a little.

491
00:32:26,844 --> 00:32:28,479
How do you fall hard enough
to cut yourself like that?

492
00:32:29,614 --> 00:32:30,515
I know, right?

493
00:32:46,230 --> 00:32:47,231
Hey, wait!

494
00:32:49,567 --> 00:32:50,401
Uh, yes?

495
00:32:50,902 --> 00:32:53,404
I only called your name.

496
00:32:53,471 --> 00:32:54,572
Don't be so nervous.

497
00:32:56,107 --> 00:32:56,941
Sorry.

498
00:33:01,045 --> 00:33:02,080
You're the reason.

499
00:33:05,883 --> 00:33:06,951
I mean,

500
00:33:08,886 --> 00:33:12,924
things worked out
because you insisted on finishing

501
00:33:12,991 --> 00:33:14,225
those presentation materials.

502
00:33:20,064 --> 00:33:21,165
Thank you.

503
00:33:51,295 --> 00:33:52,530
Come inside.

504
00:33:53,297 --> 00:33:55,133
Excuse me.

505
00:33:56,734 --> 00:33:58,036
I'm starving.

506
00:33:58,102 --> 00:34:00,304
I picked up a few things. Want to eat?

507
00:34:00,371 --> 00:34:02,273
Yes, thanks.

508
00:34:02,774 --> 00:34:04,609
-So?
-Hm?

509
00:34:04,675 --> 00:34:06,177
What's it like

510
00:34:06,244 --> 00:34:08,980
finally getting noticed by the girl
you've been in love with?

511
00:34:12,417 --> 00:34:17,989
My heart's filled with equal parts
happiness and guilt.

512
00:34:18,656 --> 00:34:19,524
What does that mean?

513
00:34:20,425 --> 00:34:22,226
You haven't done
something crazy, have you?

514
00:34:24,829 --> 00:34:26,197
What? That's scary, you know.

515
00:34:27,665 --> 00:34:28,566
Oh, thank you.

516
00:34:29,801 --> 00:34:30,835
All right.

517
00:34:31,702 --> 00:34:33,871
-Let's eat!
-Let's eat.

518
00:34:34,672 --> 00:34:37,408
So, do you actually think
you've got a chance?

519
00:34:38,509 --> 00:34:40,478
Hmm…

520
00:34:42,747 --> 00:34:43,881
-Hey.
-Mm?

521
00:34:46,184 --> 00:34:49,187
Do you think anyone
is born liking cilantro?

522
00:34:49,687 --> 00:34:50,688
Huh?

523
00:34:50,755 --> 00:34:52,990
Years ago, my boss took me
to a Thai restaurant.

524
00:34:53,057 --> 00:34:55,359
It was the first time
I'd ever eaten cilantro.

525
00:34:56,260 --> 00:34:58,096
He loved it.

526
00:34:58,162 --> 00:35:03,935
But I couldn't stand the smell
or the taste.

527
00:35:05,503 --> 00:35:07,772
I think that's how most
Japanese people feel.

528
00:35:08,372 --> 00:35:11,142
You want to be the kind of foodie
who enjoys Thai food,

529
00:35:11,209 --> 00:35:12,276
but without the cilantro.

530
00:35:12,343 --> 00:35:15,446
So you remove it
from your salad before mixing it in.

531
00:35:15,513 --> 00:35:17,582
I guess if the other person likes it,
they can just take it, right?

532
00:35:18,916 --> 00:35:21,085
But there's always someone who says,

533
00:35:22,186 --> 00:35:24,122
"Come on, just try one bite."

534
00:35:25,389 --> 00:35:28,893
As you know, I'm terrible at saying no.

535
00:35:29,694 --> 00:35:33,397
So instead of refusing,
I held my breath and ate it.

536
00:35:37,435 --> 00:35:42,140
Then the next time we went out,
he said, "Oh, yes, you liked this stuff."

537
00:35:42,206 --> 00:35:45,076
So he kept putting more on my plate.

538
00:35:45,643 --> 00:35:46,911
Where is this story going?

539
00:35:46,978 --> 00:35:48,346
Keep that up, and who knows.

540
00:35:49,180 --> 00:35:50,381
Before I knew it,

541
00:35:51,149 --> 00:35:53,651
I became the kind of man
who buys cilantro salad.

542
00:35:56,320 --> 00:35:58,189
I wasn't born liking it.

543
00:35:58,990 --> 00:36:01,926
But if something
is always there, everywhere,

544
00:36:02,894 --> 00:36:04,862
you start eating it without realizing.

545
00:36:08,666 --> 00:36:10,201
Before you know it, you actually like it.

546
00:36:13,371 --> 00:36:15,339
Do you think I could become her cilantro?

547
00:36:16,674 --> 00:36:18,943
I've been told to try it
plenty of times, and I still hate it.

548
00:36:22,613 --> 00:36:26,350
I can't believe you've stayed in love
with the same girl for 25 years.

549
00:36:26,417 --> 00:36:27,585
I could never do that.

550
00:36:28,786 --> 00:36:30,721
I mean, it's scary.

551
00:36:30,788 --> 00:36:34,425
You think it'd make her happy
if she knew it'd been 25 years?

552
00:36:35,092 --> 00:36:36,594
Me? Never.

553
00:36:38,696 --> 00:36:39,764
Mariko…

554
00:36:43,234 --> 00:36:44,902
saved me.

555
00:36:49,607 --> 00:36:51,075
I'm exhausted.

556
00:37:29,814 --> 00:37:32,450
JAPONICA WORKBOOK

557
00:37:36,954 --> 00:37:38,022
<i>May 7.</i>

558
00:37:39,357 --> 00:37:40,992
<i>Something great happened today.</i>

559
00:37:47,465 --> 00:37:48,299
<i>Like always,</i>

560
00:37:49,066 --> 00:37:53,237
<i>Nakamura and the other boys</i>
<i>from Class Three were bullying me.</i>

561
00:37:53,304 --> 00:37:54,672
-Hey, you.
-What?

562
00:37:55,273 --> 00:37:57,275
<i>A girl passing by saved me.</i>

563
00:38:01,545 --> 00:38:03,014
<i>She was so strong.</i>

564
00:38:04,248 --> 00:38:06,150
<i>So cool.</i>

565
00:38:07,051 --> 00:38:09,253
MARIKO NOSE

566
00:38:23,934 --> 00:38:25,002
<i>May 10.</i>

567
00:38:25,870 --> 00:38:29,073
<i>It looks like she goes</i>
<i>to a private elementary school.</i>

568
00:38:30,541 --> 00:38:32,510
<i>I want to thank her, but…</i>

569
00:38:49,260 --> 00:38:50,795
Cute…

570
00:39:11,949 --> 00:39:13,317
<i>I can't do it.</i>

571
00:39:13,384 --> 00:39:15,720
<i>I can't talk to her.</i>

572
00:39:18,089 --> 00:39:19,990
TRAFFIC SAFETY

573
00:39:24,228 --> 00:39:27,565
Somebody! Somebody help! Let me go!

574
00:39:28,532 --> 00:39:31,302
Somebody! Somebody! Let me go!

575
00:39:31,369 --> 00:39:33,571
Help me! Let me go!

576
00:39:36,941 --> 00:39:39,977
Somebody! Somebody, please come!

577
00:39:40,544 --> 00:39:42,313
Somebody, please help!

578
00:39:42,380 --> 00:39:44,482
Please come out! Somebody!

579
00:39:44,548 --> 00:39:47,251
-Hey! What's wrong?
-Help! That girl!

580
00:39:48,052 --> 00:39:49,653
Whoa! Hey!

581
00:39:49,720 --> 00:39:51,555
What are you doing? Stop!

582
00:39:56,026 --> 00:39:58,195
<i>Even though she was so strong,</i>

583
00:39:58,262 --> 00:39:59,697
<i>the girl who saved me…</i>

584
00:40:01,031 --> 00:40:02,833
<i>almost became a victim herself.</i>

585
00:40:06,203 --> 00:40:09,106
DIARY

586
00:40:10,975 --> 00:40:12,309
<i>I've decided.</i>

587
00:40:13,411 --> 00:40:15,880
<i>I'll protect that girl, no matter what.</i>

588
00:40:17,815 --> 00:40:18,849
MATH DRILLS

589
00:40:22,219 --> 00:40:23,287
<i>I'll always stay by her side.</i>

590
00:40:25,055 --> 00:40:26,157
<i>Always.</i>

591
00:40:27,324 --> 00:40:29,059
SOTA YUKIMURA

592
00:40:31,228 --> 00:40:32,062
SCHOOL ENTRANCE CEREMONY

593
00:40:32,129 --> 00:40:33,063
<i>April 6.</i>

594
00:40:33,631 --> 00:40:35,833
<i>I got into the same</i>
<i>middle school as Mariko.</i>

595
00:40:37,935 --> 00:40:39,570
<i>Our classrooms are as far apart</i>
<i>as they could be,</i>

596
00:40:41,405 --> 00:40:43,674
<i>but she's closer to me than ever before.</i>

597
00:40:49,480 --> 00:40:50,481
<i>I got into</i>

598
00:40:50,548 --> 00:40:54,084
<i>the same high school as Mariko</i>
<i>through the escalator system,</i>

599
00:40:54,151 --> 00:40:56,420
<i>but it won't be so easy going forward.</i>

600
00:40:56,487 --> 00:41:02,092
<i>Mariko has the best grades,</i>
<i>so I have to work very hard.</i>

601
00:41:04,695 --> 00:41:05,896
<i>I finally got into</i>

602
00:41:05,963 --> 00:41:08,499
<i>the same university as Mariko</i>
<i>a year after she did.</i>

603
00:41:09,300 --> 00:41:12,002
<i>It's sad we're in different years,</i>

604
00:41:12,069 --> 00:41:14,772
<i>but just sharing the same campus</i>
<i>makes me happy.</i>

605
00:41:18,008 --> 00:41:19,076
<i>December 3.</i>

606
00:41:19,143 --> 00:41:19,810
CAREER COUNSELING

607
00:41:19,877 --> 00:41:21,979
<i>I want to become Mariko's junior at work.</i>

608
00:41:22,046 --> 00:41:25,015
-Which company are you applying to?
-Nose Cosmetics.

609
00:41:25,950 --> 00:41:27,485
<i>I have to get hired.</i>

610
00:41:27,551 --> 00:41:28,686
NEW-HIRE ENTRANCE CEREMONY

611
00:41:28,752 --> 00:41:30,187
<i>April 2.</i>

612
00:41:30,754 --> 00:41:32,089
<i>Today was the entrance ceremony.</i>

613
00:41:34,525 --> 00:41:37,528
<i>I managed to become Mariko's junior.</i>

614
00:41:40,965 --> 00:41:43,300
<i>Mariko's only in her second year,</i>

615
00:41:43,367 --> 00:41:45,936
<i>but she's already</i>
<i>one of the company's key employees.</i>

616
00:41:47,738 --> 00:41:50,140
<i>I have to work hard too,</i>
<i>so I can get even a little closer to her.</i>

617
00:42:01,185 --> 00:42:02,820
2026/6/19 - SOTA YUKIMURA

618
00:42:14,532 --> 00:42:16,734
<i>I've been transferred</i>
<i>into the same department as Mariko.</i>

619
00:42:17,535 --> 00:42:18,702
<i>And she finally</i>

620
00:42:20,037 --> 00:42:21,705
<i>is aware of me.</i>

621
00:42:23,440 --> 00:42:25,042
<i>In these 25 years,</i>

622
00:42:25,109 --> 00:42:28,913
<i>I've never been this close to her.</i>

623
00:42:33,117 --> 00:42:34,285
<i>But this is no time to celebrate.</i>

624
00:42:34,351 --> 00:42:35,452
NO SUBJECT

625
00:42:35,519 --> 00:42:37,755
INCONSISTENCIES IN SOME EXPENSE PROCESSING
BY MR. TATEIWA

626
00:42:37,821 --> 00:42:38,789
PRELIMINARY MARKET
RESEARCH EXPENSES: 1,672,000 YEN

627
00:42:38,856 --> 00:42:42,793
<i>I must do what I need to.</i>

628
00:42:44,528 --> 00:42:46,363
President, look at this.

629
00:42:51,168 --> 00:42:53,137
SERIAL CHILD KIDNAPPER AND MURDERER
SATORU HATANO RELEASED FROM PRISON

630
00:42:57,575 --> 00:42:58,909
RELEASED AFTER 25 YEARS
EXCLUSIVE INTERVIEW

631
00:42:58,976 --> 00:43:00,678
"I HELD A GRUDGE AGAINST THE ENTIRE WORLD"

632
00:43:03,881 --> 00:43:05,549
RELEASED FROM PRISON

633
00:43:10,921 --> 00:43:15,059
<i>Darkness always tries to sneak</i>
<i>into things that shine light.</i>

634
00:43:21,565 --> 00:43:22,833
SATORU HATANO

635
00:43:22,900 --> 00:43:24,101
<i>But Mariko?</i>

636
00:43:24,935 --> 00:43:26,904
<i>You only deserve the light.</i>

637
00:43:28,005 --> 00:43:29,373
State of the body?

638
00:43:34,612 --> 00:43:37,781
Clear the way. Clear the way.

639
00:43:38,882 --> 00:43:40,250
-Hello.
-Hi.

640
00:43:40,317 --> 00:43:41,552
TAISUKE SAKURA

641
00:43:41,619 --> 00:43:43,587
-Murder?
-Most likely.

642
00:43:44,355 --> 00:43:47,891
Looks like a knife. The victim was stabbed
multiple times in the abdomen.

643
00:43:47,958 --> 00:43:51,962
Judging from the rigor mortis, they've
probably been dead for more than 24 hours.

644
00:43:53,864 --> 00:43:54,898
Who is the victim?

645
00:43:56,166 --> 00:43:59,336
Tsuyoshi Tateiwa.
An employee at Nose Cosmetics.

646
00:44:05,743 --> 00:44:07,978
<i>I won't forgive anyone</i>
<i>who gets in the way…</i>

647
00:44:10,114 --> 00:44:11,281
<i>of Mariko's life.</i>

648
00:44:14,418 --> 00:44:18,989
<i>For 25 years,</i>
<i>Mariko's the only one I've protected.</i>

649
00:44:19,490 --> 00:44:22,092
PLEASE CHECK THE SEPARATE DOCUMENT
YUKIMURA

650
00:44:22,893 --> 00:44:24,028
<i>But…</i>

651
00:44:25,229 --> 00:44:27,131
<i>destined love</i>

652
00:44:27,197 --> 00:44:29,199
<i>was never going to find me,</i>
<i>no matter how long I waited.</i>

653
00:44:31,935 --> 00:44:32,836
<i>So…</i>

654
00:44:35,639 --> 00:44:37,341
<i>I'll create destiny myself.</i>

655
00:44:37,941 --> 00:44:40,544
I'VE DECIDED

656
00:44:50,888 --> 00:44:54,158
I've decided that I'll become
the person you're destined to be with.

657
00:44:58,462 --> 00:44:59,530
NEXT TIME…

658
00:44:59,596 --> 00:45:02,599
May I speak with you for a moment?

659
00:45:07,971 --> 00:45:08,906
Subtitle translation by: Maslin Friedman
